In case you need to uninstall OpenVanilla, please follow these steps. Caution should be taken, because "
\f1 sudo rm
\f0 " is a very powerful command that might erase important system or user files. So be sure to follow this instruction letter-by-letter.\
\
1. Remove OpenVanilla Loader from your Input Method settings (in the International settings in System Preferences)\
2. Get into shell (Terminal.app will do)\
3. Use the folloing commands:\
\
